      • getPayload

        public <T> Optional<T> getPayload​(Class<T> payloadClass)
        Gets the payload of expected type T, in it's Optional container.

        This is a convenience method meant for callers who know the expected type of the payload and don't want to cast it manually. This means that if the expected type T of the payload is different than the actual type, then an Optional.empty() will be returned.

        Type Parameters:
        T - the input type of the payload
        Parameters:
        payloadClass - the expected Class type of the payload
        Returns:
        the Optional containing the expected payload type

      • getPayloadAs

        public <T> T getPayloadAs​(Class<T> payloadClass)
        Gets the payload of expected type T.

        This is a convenience method meant for callers who know that the payload is present and also know the actual type of the payload. This means that if the expected type T of the payload is different than the actual type OR the payload isn't present, then an IllegalArgumentException will be thrown

        Type Parameters:
        T - the input type of the payload
        Parameters:
        payloadClass - the expected Class type of the payload
        Returns:
        the payload of type T
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the expected payload is of a different type, or isn't present
